sudokuGame

Class Individual

  • java.lang.Object
    • sudokuGame.Individual
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>, Variable
    Direct Known Subclasses:
    BoardIndividual

    public abstract class Individual
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<java.lang.Object>, Variable
    Individual abstract class is representing one player (individual), set of genes, that trying to solve the gaven sudoku board, the program will end if one individual success to solve the sudoku board, and if NO one success to solve the sudoku then we use evolutionary algorithm (next generation) method to create new generation of individuals that trying to solve the sudoku. Note: there are NO major deference between Individual class and BoardIndividual class except wo decided to design and put everything related to the Tree-Based Genetic programing and recursive methods in this class. And everything related to solving the board and in BoardIndividual, we could put all the methods and all the variables in one class.
    Version:
    1.0
    Author:
    Abedalrhman Nsasra
    See Also:
    BoardIndividual, Population, Node, TerminalOrPrimitive, Genetic Programming

      • run

        double run(int row,
           int col,
           int key,
           int[][] board,
           java.util.Hashtable<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Double>[][] gradeboard)
        This method compute the grade for the specified number (key parameter) that can inserted (without conflict), in the specified empty cells (board[row, col] parameters). The grades are computed according to the tree, the tree give the specified option, in the specified index their grade.
        Parameters:
        row - the specific row index that we want to compute the grade for the options that can inserted in this index.
        col - the specific column index that we want to compute the grade for the options that can inserted in this index.
        key - the number that we want to compute his grade as a solution in the board in board[row, col].
        board - 2D array that represent the sudoku board.
        gradeboard - reference to matrix of hash tables that represent in every index in the matrix which numbers can be inserted without conflict as a keys in the hash table and grade as a value for every key that represent how good this option as solution, we choose smaller grade is better but you could choose larger is better, it will not change the solution.
        Returns:
        a grade for the key (number) as a solution in the index board[row, col], the return value is a grade to tell us how much good this solution.

      • reGenerateFullTree

        public void reGenerateFullTree()
        generate the tree of the current instance from the beginning, totally new generating, using generateFullTree, with the same instance height. NO optimizing for the implantation of this method, we totally create new tree, if you want to optimize the memory and get better performance, you should reimplement this method.

      • createFullTree

        protected void createFullTree(int height,
                              @NotNull
                              Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> node)
        Generate full tree-based Genetic Programing, receive a height and root node, must be NOT null, and generate a random primitive instance for the root, in case the height is greater that 0, and then call createSubTree with root node, and height as arguments. In case the required height is 0 (it's mean we need tree with only one node), the method will generate a random Terminal instance for the node, and done. This method use createSubTree recursive method as a help method, that create the rest of the tree in recursive calling.
        Parameters:
        height - the height of the tree that you want to generate.
        node - the root of the tree you want to generate, the root must be NOT null.

      • createSubTree

        private void createSubTree(int height,
                           Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> node)
        Recursive method that create a sub tree, you must send her NOT null reference, as a root node and then this method will generate a full tree with gaven height. This method is a recursive, so we prefer to implement it in a functional style.
        Parameters:
        height - the height of the tree that we want to generate in a recursive way.
        node - the root node, this root must be NOT null, you must create the root externally and send it as a parameter.

      • copyFullTree

        protected Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> copyFullTree(Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> sourceNode)
        receive a source root node as a parameter and then clone the whole tree and return it. The cloning is deep cloning so we create totally new tree. This method use copySubTree as a help method, here we clone only root node and call copySubTree with the new node of the root and the old root (the actual tree) as a parameters to let the copySubTree method to do the rest of the work (cloning).
        Parameters:
        sourceNode - the reference of the source root that we want to clone.
        Returns:
        totally new tree as a result of cloning.

      • copySubTree

        private static void copySubTree(Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> sourceNode,
                                Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> decisionNode)
        This method receive as arguments source node and decision node and clone the content of the source node into decision node, the coping is done in a recursive way, so we sent the two trees in the method as parameters. If decisionNode is NOT only root(NOT only one node) then the method will ignore and throw all the rest of the tree to GC.
        Parameters:
        sourceNode - is the reference of the root that we want to copy.
        decisionNode - is the reference of the root that hold the copied tree.

      • ConvertTreeToPrefixExpression

        private java.lang.StringBuilder ConvertTreeToPrefixExpression(Node<TerminalOrPrimitive> node)
        Build a string that represent out tree-Based GP in prefix expression, the building is done in recursive way, and in efficient way. we return in the end StringBuilder instance, to get the the String you need just to call toString method and you will get the String, remember this is just help method.
        Parameters:
        node - is the reference of the node that we reach in the recursive calling.
        Returns:
        StringBuilder instance that represent out tree in prefix expression.
